1
00:00:00,333 --> 00:00:07,500
The room, after I entered through the door here,
they brought me in kneeling, of course

2
00:00:08,083 --> 00:00:14,291
My hands were bound behind my back,
blindfolded, of course I could not see

3
00:00:14,875 --> 00:00:19,541
Any of them, except once
when one of them took my information

4
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:25,458
He told me, you are talking about us
and disrespecting the mujahideen

5
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:29,875
Of course I said, no sheikh,
and he said, will you not stop running your mouth

6
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:34,666
So he punched me here,
I think there were two people behind me

7
00:00:35,666 --> 00:00:42,458
He hit me and when they helped me stand up,
he struck me here on my cheekbone and broke it

8
00:00:43,958 --> 00:00:47,708
And when they helped me stand up,
he beat me with the green hose

9
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:53,250
Known as the Lakhdar Brahimi, which became
a notorious torture weapon, he beat me on my back

10
00:00:54,125 --> 00:00:57,833
He said, take him to disciplinary,
and I did not know what disciplinary was

11
00:00:57,875 --> 00:01:03,708
I expected they might have hoists and
<i>balingo</i> [hoist for suspension], then they took me to disciplinary

12
00:01:04,791 --> 00:01:11,291
The disciplinary cell was a room roughly 70 cm wide,
by two meters long

13
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:18,875
Just like this, nothing in it
except one blanket to sleep on the floor with

14
00:01:19,416 --> 00:01:22,333
Interviewer: During your imprisonment,
how many times did they interrogate you?

15
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:26,791
They interrogated me approximately
15 or 16 times

16
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:33,166
Of course, because I was denying the charges
and denying everything, any claim at all

17
00:01:33,166 --> 00:01:40,666
Because I knew, we were afraid of execution
and things like that

18
00:01:41,458 --> 00:01:48,583
Because we felt an unnatural terror due to
the abnormal methods of torture

19
00:01:49,541 --> 00:01:57,041
Abnormal beatings, humiliation, of course
the disciplinary cell alone equaled all other forms of torture, it was the worst

20
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:59,166
It was worse than all other methods of torture

21
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:03,750
Interviewer: Was there any audio
or video recording? Or did you not notice?

22
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:08,458
I do not know, only once they removed
my <i>tamasha</i> [blindfold], they lifted it

23
00:02:08,791 --> 00:02:15,083
Here I noticed two people, I even looked away
from them and kept my eyes fixed on the ground

24
00:02:15,208 --> 00:02:18,666
Even him, I could not look at his face
and he was masked, I could not look at him

25
00:02:19,208 --> 00:02:21,958
Two people sitting in the corner
using laptops

26
00:02:22,791 --> 00:02:29,416
They did not interfere or approach, and two people,
as I later learned, stand behind you during interrogation

27
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:35,708
The interrogator was sitting here like this,
and next to him he placed

28
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:41,416
The stick and the whip, his weapons ready,
his torture tools

29
00:02:42,291 --> 00:02:45,458
Interviewer: Who were the interrogators?
And what was their accent?

30
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:49,083
Interviewer: What were their questions?
What type of questions did they ask you?

31
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:53,583
Their accent was local,
meaning the interrogator was not a foreigner

32
00:02:54,916 --> 00:03:01,000
There was one person whose accent was not fully
Arabic, but he was not an interrogator

33
00:03:01,041 --> 00:03:04,541
That was only once,
meaning he came only one time

34
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:10,666
The types of questions: What do you know?
Do you have connections outside? Who is so-and-so?

35
00:03:10,708 --> 00:03:15,916
And who is so-and-so? On the phone for example,
he reads names, who is this person, and this person

36
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:20,708
Where does this one live? What does he do?
Do you know anyone in the Free Syrian Army?

37
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:26,416
Or anyone in the areas controlled
by the Assad regime? Or anyone in the party?

38
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:31,416
A party called the Syrian Democratic Forces,
the SDF

39
00:03:32,416 --> 00:03:36,791
I told him, I do not know anything,
I am someone who does not mix with anyone

40
00:03:38,541 --> 00:03:46,541
Interviewer: Did they have a lot of information
about you? Did they know things about you that nobody else knew?

41
00:03:46,583 --> 00:03:51,083
Interviewer: Did they have methods or intelligence
officers who brought them information?

42
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:57,708
Of course, my detention was because of what I said
in front of someone who gave them the information

43
00:03:58,125 --> 00:04:05,625
Information about me, ordinary information,
of course they have information about most of the locals

44
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:13,375
It was ordinary information, they knew my job
and where I live, nothing more

45
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:21,416
Interviewer: Did they offer you to work with them
or join them in exchange for releasing you from prison?

46
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:29,666
No, that matter, they assumed that we,
and people like me

47
00:04:29,708 --> 00:04:34,583
Among the prisoners, especially in this place,
would never cooperate with them

48
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:41,541
They always viewed us as a dagger in their back,
of course that was their perspective

49
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:46,375
Except once, they tried changing the interrogation
approach from beating

50
00:04:47,625 --> 00:04:52,833
He brought me once, stood me up like this,
and moved me slightly to the left

51
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:56,416
Then he removed my blindfold
from my face for the first time

52
00:04:56,625 --> 00:05:03,250
He was sitting there, wearing a Chechen-style tunic,
and a desert-colored mask, not black

53
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:08,083
Behind me were two guards, dressed in black,
wearing black masks

54
00:05:08,416 --> 00:05:14,666
Next to me was a person I know who lives in Tabqa,
I prefer not to mention his name

55
00:05:15,541 --> 00:05:21,250
He spoke to him and said, did anyone beat you?
He said, no, no sheikh

56
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:26,875
Did anyone harm you or speak to you?
He said no, so he said take him to his room, give him what he wants, and let him call his mother

57
00:05:28,375 --> 00:05:32,541
After he left, he said to me, do you know
why we did not beat him? I said, no sheikh, I do not know

58
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:41,000
He said, because he was cooperating with us
and told us everything, so you be like that and we will make it easier for you

59
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:45,625
I told him, I have told you everything I have,
there is nothing to add

60
00:05:46,208 --> 00:05:53,500
And that is when the beating started,
he beat me that day as if I had provoked him with those words

61
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:59,291
When I got out, my entire back was blue,
all of it

62
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:07,541
He said, take him and discipline him,
in his words, until he becomes a human being, then I was taken back to disciplinary

63
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:12,000
Interviewer: Did they threaten you with anything,
like harming your family outside?

64
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:18,250
They threatened me with my brother,
one of my brothers, that they would bring him and detain him

65
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:24,083
I told him, he is a minor,
he was 17 or 18 years old at the time

66
00:06:24,416 --> 00:06:27,083
I told him, he is a minor, he has nothing,
even if you bring him

67
00:06:27,083 --> 00:06:29,375
I said, sheikh, I have nothing,
I have told you everything

68
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:34,791
Of course, at that point I understood
this was a tactic to provoke me into talking

69
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:38,625
He was trying to provoke me
so that I would talk to him

70
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:43,708
I told him, if you want to bring him then bring him,
he is a minor who knows nothing

71
00:06:44,291 --> 00:06:49,625
Interviewer: Did they threaten you with execution?
Or with a longer prison sentence if you did not confess?

72
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:55,375
No, they did not threaten me with execution,
because he would tell me, confess

73
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:59,333
And undergo one of our <i>sharia</i> courses
and then you will be released, here they do not threaten

74
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:02,791
Here the death threats, from what I would hear
of course

75
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:07,333
While I was in my solitary cell,
I could hear them during interrogations, the screaming and torture

76
00:07:07,916 --> 00:07:11,416
Those who confessed, they would tell them,
I will execute you on such-and-such day

77
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:13,916
After a few days,
we will throw you at such-and-such roundabout

78
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:19,958
There were things that happened
that I found deeply shocking

79
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:26,250
One such thing was a prisoner who cursed God,
meaning he blasphemed, as we say

80
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:31,291
I could hear him being told,
are you doing this to hasten your execution?

81
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:35,583
I will extend your time and keep you
under torture for an extra month just for that

82
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:40,916
This matter, to this very moment I am shocked by it,
to this very moment I cannot believe it

83
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:48,833
I even asked one of the prisoners who was here
with me after ISIS's reign ended, I asked him, and he said, yes I heard it

84
00:07:49,416 --> 00:07:55,666
I heard that too, I asked him, did you hear
the same thing as me or was I imagining it? He said, I heard it with my own ears
